-- Danish July forex reserves rise to 440.9 bln DKK
-- By Teis Jensen
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 10:05AM EDT
-- None



COPENHAGEN, Aug 4 (Reuters) - Denmark's foreign exchange reserves, a monetary policy tool, rose to 440.9 billion Danish crowns ($794 billion) in July from 438.2 in June, the central bank said on Monday.

The bank said it did not intervene in the foreign exchange market in July to steady the crown.